<dec f='linux-4.14.y/include/rdma/ib_verbs.h' l='2961' type='int ib_modify_srq(struct ib_srq * srq, struct ib_srq_attr * srq_attr, enum ib_srq_attr_mask srq_attr_mask)'/>
<doc f='linux-4.14.y/include/rdma/ib_verbs.h' l='2949'>/**
 * ib_modify_srq - Modifies the attributes for the specified SRQ.
 * @srq: The SRQ to modify.
 * @srq_attr: On input, specifies the SRQ attributes to modify.  On output,
 *   the current values of selected SRQ attributes are returned.
 * @srq_attr_mask: A bit-mask used to specify which attributes of the SRQ
 *   are being modified.
 *
 * The mask may contain IB_SRQ_MAX_WR to resize the SRQ and/or
 * IB_SRQ_LIMIT to set the SRQ&apos;s limit and request notification when
 * the number of receives queued drops below the limit.
 */</doc>
